Release notes for 3.2.0-2
This release is a beta release and should not be used for a production site.

- All text strings in eZ publish has been freezed and can now be translated before the final release.
- The admin email address can now be controlled by one ini setting making it easier to maintain.
- The new script functionality has been integrated with all scripts in eZ publish making them
  easier to use as well as making it easier to maintain them. Try -h or --help on all scripts
  to see new possible options.
- The old API reference view has been brought in a similar way as it was in the old SDK.
  To access it you must enter the url reference/view/ez
- The setup has been given an overhaul with new help texts, better user interface and some bugfixes.
- The command line utility for managing packages (ezpm.php) has been updated. The missing install command
  was added, this means that it's now possible to install package archives from the command line.
  Also the content class handling was fixed.
- The search statistics page now has a button to reset the stats if this is needed.
- The webdav library has been improved and should now even work without the use of rewrite rules but only
  for some clients. The need for having register_globals set to on is now removed.
